<section id="To_assign_Policy_Profiles_to_a_Virtual_Machine" remap="TID_14789">
	<title>Assigning Policy Profiles to a Virtual Machine</title>
	<procedure>
		<title>To assign policy profiles to a virtual machine</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu><guisubmenu>Virtual Machines</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, check the virtual machines you need to assign policy profiles to.
			</para> 
			<!--mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata align="center" fileref="images/1951.png"/>
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject-->
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1941.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Policy</guilabel>), and then click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1952.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject>(<guilabel>Manage Policies</guilabel>).
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				From the <guilabel>Select Policy Profiles</guilabel> area, click on the triangle next to a desired policy profile to expand it and see its member policies.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Check the policy profiles you need to apply to the host. It will turn blue to show that its assignment state has changed.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Save</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>